        "title": "fix: expand unsafe host env denylist",
        "body": "## Summary\n\n- Expands the shared host environment safety policy to reject additional interpreter startup and search-path variables before they reach host command execution.\n- Regenerates the macOS host environment policy from the shared JSON source so app and Node-host sanitizers stay aligned.\n- Updates focused regression coverage and user-facing docs that enumerate the blocked environment override classes.\n- Intentionally does not change the sanitizer control flow; this keeps the existing policy-driven behavior and only expands the denylist data.\n\nAI-assisted: yes.\n\n## Linked context\n\nNo public issue linked in this PR body.\n\n## Real behavior proof (required for external PRs)\n\n- Behavior addressed: Host environment overrides for additional interpreter startup/search-path variables are rejected by the existing node-host `system.run` handler before process execution.\n- Real environment tested: Local OpenClaw checkout on Linux using the actual `handleSystemRunInvoke` runtime path and a real child process spawn for the safe case.\n- Exact steps or command run after this patch: `pnpm exec tsx /tmp/openclaw-system-run-proof-91618.ts`\n- Evidence after fix: The blocked request reported `SYSTEM_RUN_DENIED: environment override rejected (blocked override keys: BASHOPTS, FPATH, KSH_ENV, TCLLIBPATH)` with `executed: false`; the safe request reported `executed: true`, `ok: true`, `stdout: \"ok\\nBASHOPTS_UNSET\\n\"`, and `exitCode: 0`.\n- Observed result after fix: The four risky env overrides are rejected before `system.run` executes, while an ordinary `OPENCLAW_PROOF_SAFE=ok` env override still reaches the spawned process.\n- What was not tested: Full gateway-to-paired-node WebSocket round trip and full repository CI were not run locally.\n- Proof limitations or environment constraints: The proof uses the real node-host handler and real process execution in a local checkout, but not a separately paired node service.\n- Before evidence: Existing tests did not cover these variables in the shared policy baseline.\n\n## Tests and validation\n\n- `node scripts/run-vitest.mjs src/infra/host-env-security.test.ts src/infra/host-env-security.policy-parity.test.ts src/infra/host-env-security.reported-baseline.test.ts`\n- `node scripts/generate-host-env-security-policy-swift.mjs --check`\n- `git diff --check`\n- `scripts/pr review-tests 91618 src/infra/host-env-security.test.ts src/infra/host-env-security.policy-parity.test.ts src/infra/host-env-security.reported-baseline.test.ts`\n- `timeout 1800 .agents/skills/autoreview/scripts/autoreview --mode branch --base origin/main`\n- `pnpm exec tsx /tmp/openclaw-system-run-proof-91618.ts`\n\nRegression coverage was added for dangerous-key classification, inherited sanitization, override sanitization, diagnostics, reported baseline coverage, and generated macOS policy parity.\n\n## Risk checklist\n\nDid user-visible behavior change? `Yes`\n\nDid config, environment, or migration behavior change? `Yes`\n\nDid security, auth, secrets, network, or tool execution behavior change? `Yes`\n\nHighest-risk area: Host command execution environment filtering.\n\nRisk mitigation: The change reuses the existing denylist policy mechanism, keeps ordinary credential/proxy/server-specific variables unaffected, adds focused tests for the expanded policy surface, and includes runtime proof that safe env overrides still pass.\n\n## Current review state\n\nNext action: Wait for automated CI, ClawSweeper re-review, and maintainer review.\n\nStill waiting on: GitHub CI and any maintainer-requested broader validation.\n\nBot or reviewer comments addressed: ClawSweeper proof request addressed by adding runtime `system.run` handler proof to this PR body.\n",
